text: The 1930 New Mexico gubernatorial election took place on November 4, 1930, in order to elect the Governor of New Mexico. Incumbent Republican Richard C. Dillon was term-limited, and could not run for reelection to a third consecutive term. ==General election== ===Results=== ==References== gubernatorial 1930 New Mexico Category:November 1930 events
title: 1930 New Mexico gubernatorial election
